Both men and women see a beneficial marriage relationship as one where both spouses fulfil their obligations to one another in a mutually supportive way; women however, are significantly more likely than men to underscore the importance of companionship, life-long commitment and finding divorce unacceptable as key elements to achieving a healthy marriage (p<0.05).[5]
